F08. Can I submit a late application?
Late applications may be accepted if places are still available and it is subject to the discretion of relevant academic unit. You are advised to submit your application as early as possible. For some programmes, applications are considered on a rolling basis. Review of applications will start before the deadline and continue until all places are filled. You are advised to check whether the respective academic units accept late applications before submitting your application.
F09. What documents do I need to submit besides the application form?
A complete set of application submitted online should include*:
an application form;
an applicant statement, if applicable;
a supplementary form for some programmes, if applicable;

