Failing to provide the required documents may result in your unsuccessful enrolment in the programme. If documents provided are found to be falsiï¬ed, unclear, misleading or inconsistent with the qualiï¬cations stated in your application, or do not fulï¬ll the requirements for admission, the University will have to withdraw your admission offer and all paid fees will not be refunded. All applicants are required to meet the stipulated entrance requirements of the programme. The University reserves the right to revoke/void any offer if applicants fail to meet the entrance requirements or provide the original documentations for verification.
